<blockquote>"More organizations will be pushed to reduce costs, improve the quality of products and services, locate new opportunities for growth, and increase productivity."</blockquote>

<p>This is as true today (2022) as it was in 1996 when first written.</p>

<p>[book:Leading Change|51370] is a blueprint for the cost/quality/growth/productivity challenge that virtually all organziations must confront. Start with the eight errors that most organizations face when wresling with these issues. Then, outline a plan to combat these errors. Simple and powerful, yet by no means easy.</p>



